snippet: Iran reached an agreement on Tuesday with world powers to resume the stuttering dialogue over its disputed nuclear program later this month in Kazakhstan, officials said.
abstract: Iran agrees to resume talks over its disputed nuclear program this February in Kazakhstan.

byline.original: By MICHAEL R. GORDON and ALAN COWELL
byline.contributor: Michael R. Gordon reported from Washington and Alan Cowell from London. Rick Gladstone contributed reporting from New York.

lead_paragraph: Iran reached an agreement on Tuesday with world powers to resume the stuttering dialogue over its disputed nuclear program later this month in Kazakhstan, officials said.

headline.seo: Iran Nuclear Talks to Resume This Month
